Kingston is a rural locality of the Shire of Bridgetownâ€“Greenbushes in the South West region of Western Australia. The locality is predominantly forested, with the Greater Kingston National Park in the east and the Palgarup State Forest in the south.
It is on the traditional land of the Noongar people.
